<ContentLayout title="Coming Soon">
  <Section>
    <Comment> last updated for AT Uth Duna </Comment>

    <p>
      These are the current endgame builds for Title Update 2, which added Seregios and Lagiacrus.
      All of these assume you've completed the main story and have access to the highest rarity
      Artian weapons, plus pretty much all decorations and armor pieces.
    </p>

    <p>
      They require you to have completed the main story and unlocked the ability to craft the
      highest rarity Artian weapons, as well as having access to pretty much all decorations and
      armor pieces in the game.
    </p>

    <SectionSubTitle title="Weapons" />

    <p>
      Artian weapons are still the best option in the game by a wide margin. They all come with
      three level-3 slots, which lets you stack the weapon skills that lance really needs. The
      reinforcement system also gives them the best stats for almost every element or status, making
      most craftable lances pretty obsolete.
    </p>

    <p>
      When crafting new Artian weapons, try to get three parts with the same element or status, plus
      an attack infusion. This basically guarantees you to get the element you want while maximizing
      the attack production bonus.
    </p>

    <p>
      For reinforcement bonuses, aim for 1 sharpness and 4 attack. Even if you only get 2-3 attack
      reinforcements, it'll still outperform the craftable alternatives.
    </p>

    <p>Here's how to use those 3 weapon decoration slots:</p>
